  <p>The above angles are measured using <term>degrees</term>. 
  An angle <m>\theta</m> may also be measured using <em>radians</em>. 
  The radian measurement corresponds to a distance around the circumference, <m>C</m>, of the unit circle (<m>C' = 2\pi</m>).</p>

  <p>Let us measure an arc on the unit circle starting at (1,0) of length <m>\frac{\pi}{4}</m> and ending at a point <m>P</m>. 
  If we draw a ray from the origin through point <m>P</m>, we have formed an angle <m>\theta</m>, where <m>\theta</m> = <m>\frac{\pi}{4}</m>radians.</p>

